0, 21:9) without text or buttons being obscured.']}, 'implementation_considerations': {'complexity_assessment': 'Low', 'complexity_factors': ['Standard UI implementation using engine-native components.', 'No complex logic or state management required.', 'Dependent on receiving the final text content.'], 'technical_risks': ['Minimal risk. The primary risk is the text content becoming outdated if game features related to data storage change in the future. Storing the text in an easily updatable resource file mitigates this.'], 'integration_points': ['Main Menu UI canvas.', "Game's central UI navigation/manager system."]}, 'testing_requirements': {'testing_types': ['Integration', 'E2E', 'Accessibility'], 'test_scenarios': ['Verify button on main menu opens the correct view.', 'Verify the view can be closed and returns to the main menu.', 'Verify the full text is present and readable.', 'Verify scrolling functionality on long text.', 'Verify keyboard/controller navigation to open and close the view.', 'Verify UI scaling and appearance on different resolutions and aspect ratios.'], 'test_data_needs': ['The final, approved privacy statement text.', 'A placeholder text that is intentionally longer than the viewable area to test scrolling.'], 'testing_tools': ['Unity Editor for UI inspection.', 'Manual testing on target platform.']}, 'definition_of_done': ['All acceptance criteria validated and passing', 'Code reviewed and approved by team', 'Unit tests implemented and passing', 'Integration testing completed successfully', 'User interface reviewed and approved by a UX designer or project lead', 'Performance requirements verified', 'Security requirements validated', 'Final, approved privacy statement text is implemented and sourced from a resource file', 'Story deployed and verified in staging environment'], 'planning_information': {'story_points': '1', 'priority': 'Medium', 'sprint_considerations': ['This is a good task for a developer focused on UI. It is blocked until the final text content is provided.'], 'release_impact': ['This feature is considered a requirement for a professional, trustworthy V1.0 public release.']}}